video_description: What happened to the electric mail trucks? They’re way behind schedule. A multibillion-dollar program to buy electric vehicles for the U.S. Postal Service is far behind its original schedule, plagued by manufacturing mishaps and supplier infighting that threaten a cornerstone of outgoing President Joe Biden’s fight against climate change. The Postal Service is slated to purchase 60,000 “Next Generation Delivery Vehicles,” or NGDVs — mostly electric — from defense contractor Oshkosh, which has a long history of producing military and heavy industrial vehicles, but not postal trucks. Congress provided $3 billion for the nearly $10 billion project in the 2022 Inflation Reduction Act, one of Biden’s chief legislative accomplishments. But as of November, the Postal Service had received only 93 of the Oshkosh trucks, the agency told The Washington Post — far fewer than the 3,000 expected by now. Significant manufacturing difficulties that were not disclosed to the Postal Service for more than a year have stymied production, according to internal company records and four people with knowledge of the events, speaking on the condition of anonymity to avoid professional reprisals. Caption from article by Jacob Bogage.

FBI SAYS: Encrypt your messages If you don’t use secure messaging apps, now is a good time to start.U.S. officials say a massive Chinese hacking campaign, dubbed Salt Typhoon, has compromised the communications of an unknown number of Americans.  The FBI and Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) have recommended that people switch to encrypted messaging and phone call options.Most people don’t think too much about what apps they use to make calls or send texts. They assume some amount of security and privacy is built into their devices or provided by their phone carriers. With no timeline on when the networks will be safe, and no guarantee it can’t happen again, it may be time to switch your chats to something safer. We’ll get you started.
How much are you swiping each day?  Probably around 18. Here’s the latest from our data reporters on what we learned about your TikTok data!

U.S. officials moved Tuesday to protect the monarch, an iconic orange-and-black butterfly famous for its marathon migration across North America, under the Endangered Species Act. The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service’s proposal to designate the tiny migrating butterfly as threatened with extinction could have enormous consequences for landowners across its huge range, which extends across much of the Lower 48 as the monarch makes its epic annual flight from the mountains of Mexico through the United States and into Canada. TikTok based on reporting by Dino Grandoni.

Could MORE Chinese products be banned?! A combination of unique factors has put some Chinese technologies on U.S. lawmakers’ naughty list. Companies from China are increasingly global technology trendsetters, including in important areas like electric vehicles and artificial intelligence. It’s hard to buy an internet-connected home device that doesn’t run on Chinese technology. Technologies that originate in other countries considered adversaries of the United States, such as Iran and Russia, are mostly irrelevant in the United States. There’s also a fuzzy line in China between private corporations and the government. U.S. officials believe that TikTok or other Chinese companies would have to comply if Beijing ordered them to hand over data they have on Americans, to spy on us, or to spread Chinese Communist Party propaganda.

A judge rejected the sale of InfoWars to The Onion (12/11/2024). U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Christopher Lopez ruled Tuesday that the November court-ordered auction of Jones’s website lacked transparency. The decision capped a two-day hearing that stretched late into the night in U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Christopher Lopez’s Houston courtroom. “I don’t think anyone acted in bad faith here. I think everyone was trying to buy an asset and put their best foot forward and play by the rules,” Lopez said as he delivered his decision. The judge took issue with the lack of transparency from the sealed bidding process selected by the court-appointed trustee Christopher Murray, who was overseeing the sale of Jones’s assets. The judge added that he was troubled that the process, however well intended, “did not maximize value in any way, based on the record before me.” In a statement, the Onion’s CEO, Ben Collins, expressed disappointment that the ruling did not clear a path forward for any bidder, but he indicated it would continue its efforts toward acquiring Infowars. “It is part of our larger mission to make a better, funnier internet, regardless of the outcome,” the statement said. Caption from article by Kim Bellware and Niha Masih.

The Murdoch family is fighting over future control of Fox News and the Wall Street Journal. Rupert Murdoch wanted to change the terms of his family’s trust to ensure that his son Lachlan would be his successor upon his death, but a Nevada probate commissioner rejected his bid. Murdoch, 93, initiated the effort to change the terms of the trust last year to preserve the conservative orientation of his sprawling media empire. As first reported by the New York Times this summer, the elder Murdoch was concerned that a “lack of consensus” among his three other older children would have financial consequences for the company. But probate commissioner Edmund “Joe” Gorman Jr. ruled against the effort, deeming it a “carefully crafted charade,” the New York Times reported on Monday afternoon. The case will now move to a district judge who could choose to affirm the recommendation, deny it or send it back for additional inquiry. Caption from original article by Jeremy Barr and Sarah Ellison.

Authorities have charged Luigi Mangione, 26, with the m*rder of Brian Thompson, the UnitedHealthcare chief executive who was killed in New York City last week. Mangione was denied bail Tuesday and will remain in a state prison in Pennsylvania. His lawyer said he does not consent to being extradited to New York. New York police say Mangione k!lled Thompson, 50, with a fatal shot to his torso. According to a complaint made public Tuesday, police think Mangione is the person who killed Thompson based on evidence that includes “written admissions about the crime” as well as surveillance footage. Authorities arrested Mangione on Monday in central Pennsylvania after a five-day manhunt that began when Thompson was shot on a Manhattan sidewalk Wednesday. Mangione, who was arraigned in a courthouse near Altoona, Pennsylvania, faces five counts in that state, including carrying a firearm without a license, possessing instruments of a crime and providing law enforcement with false identification. The m*rder count and other charges were filed in New York.

Trumps BIG budget plans President-elect Donald Trump this week tapped Musk and former GOP presidential candidate Vivek Ramaswamy to stand up a commission to make recommendations by 2026 for cutting government spending and regulation. Dubbed the “Department of Government Efficiency,” or DOGE, the commission’s structure and specific goals are not yet clear. (Under current law, only Congress can actually cut spending. Trump’s team is exploring how it could implement some DOGE recommendations without congressional approval, The Washington Post reported this week.)Musk has publicly sparred with agencies over the years, including those that have taken actions against his businesses. For example, this week he elevated a call for “defanging” both the Securities and Exchange Commission and the Federal Trade Commission, an agency he has accused of “overreach” and being “weaponiz[ed] … for censorship & political machinations.”

voice_to_text: please tell me you know who this man is he's a bit mysterious the utimate enigma considered one of the greatest songwriters of all time it's Bob Dylan 😎 there is a movie coming out about him a biopic called A Complete Unknown starring Timothée Chalamet who's playing a young Bob Dylan A Complete Unknown is diving into Dylan's meteoric rise between 1961 and 1965 I thought why not dig into the real Bob Dylan you know the one behind the harmonica and the poetry the one that dated muses got married in secret and pulled out a surprise divorce kid out of nowhere so buckle up buttercups it's about to get messy before Bob Dylan became Bob Dylan he was Bobby Zimmerman from Minnesota and Echo Helstrom was the it girl of hiving high school Echo was the blueprint of the bohemian type women that he would surround himself with later and many believe she was the inspiration for some of his early music fast forward to Greenwich Village in the early 60s where Bob meets Suze Rotolo the woman who will forever be immortalized on the cover of his Freewheelin’ album Suze was an artist and a political activist who introduced Bob to leftist politics which influenced his music in the film Elle Fanning is playing a character named Sylvie which is based on Suze can you see it their relationship was passionate but very messy Bob's career was taking off and he had a wandering eye enter folk singer Joan Baez she was already successful with her own album and she invited Bob to perform with her they started bumping uglies but soon he began to treat her like she was extra baggage she said he was demoralizing and they broke up later he apologized to her and they began performing together again I think we're gonna see this dynamic in the film as well by the mid 60s Bob's career is on fire and so is his love life enter Sara Lownds Sara was a former Playboy Bunny and a single mom they got married in 1965 Bob adopted her first daughter Maria and together they had four children three boys one girl Jesse Dylan who is a filmmaker daughter Anna Dylan who unlike some of her brothers is living more of a private life Sam Dylan who also stays a bit more private and then we've got Jakob Dylan also a singer and a songwriter lead vocalist of the Wallflowers who to me looks like a cuter version of his dad Bob and Sara were together for 12 years they grew apart he cheated on her they got divorced and Bob was doing his thing Bob was in a relationship with a woman named Ruth Tyrangiel this could be her or that could be her all I know is they were together for about 17 years and she was considered his common law wife here's where things get messy because around the same time he was in a relationship with his backup singer named Carolyn Dennis together they had a daughter they named Desiree and then they got married in secret no one knew about it until they filed for divorce no one knew they had another daughter Carolyn said they purposely left his last name off of the birth certificate so that Desiree could decide to add it if she wanted to later she also said that implying that he kept Desiree a secret was a huge insult and that he was a great father to her all I know is people have been obsessed with who he's dated some say Edie Sedgwick he denies it he had a thing with singer Nico apparently he asked Mavis Staples to marry him she said no he was a ladies man Bob Dylan is a living legend and I cannot wait to see this movie A Complete Unknown

voice_to_text: my heart felt physical pain watching this tears streaming down my face Super/Man the Christopher Reeve Story maybe I'm late to the game watching this 10/10 cannot recommend enough we learned about his parents how he grew up he went to Cornell then he went to Juilliard here he met Robin Williams they had a lifelong friendship boom he's hired for Superman the hottest Clark Kent he's filming in London where he meets Gae Exton they begin a relationship because his parents’ relationship was not a great example Christopher could not commit but he was living in London with Gae together they had two children son Matthew and daughter Alexandra Christopher is busier and busier doing Superman's 1 2 3 and 4 in 1987 Gae and Christopher decide to separate he moves back to the US and he sees his children on holidays later that same year Christopher meets a young singer actress named Dana Morosini they were a couple living together but again Christopher had commitment issues Christopher was Superman he was 6’4 buff athletic very physical he was a pilot he wind surfed sailed boats he learned how to ride horses for a project he was in even though he was allergic after about five years Christopher finally decided to propose to Dana and they got married in 1992 later that same year they had a son they named William in this documentary they talk about the tragic accident that happened in 1995 he was competing at a horse show when right before the third jump his horse just refused completely stopped Christopher was thrown off the horse fell directly on his head broken snapped just like a noose half an inch to the left he would have been gone half an inch to the right he would have just gotten up his first and second vertebrae completely destroyed his spinal cord was severely damaged he was paralyzed from the neck down could not breathe without a ventilator this documentary talks about how his own mother wanted to pull the plug and he wanted to unalive himself he didn't wanna go on any longer but Dana looked into his eyes told him she was never going anywhere and said you are still you and I love you listen tears are gonna stream down your face and then they talk about how Robin Williams went to the hospital to go visit him made him laugh the entire world wanted to know what happened to Christopher because he almost did not make it and with the help of Robin Williams and his wife and Christopher's wife Dana Christopher Reeve was able to make an appearance at the 1996 Oscars watching this reminded me to be grateful for your health for all of the little things does anyone remember this Super Bowl commercial from the year 2000 where Christopher Reeve looked like he was walking on his own two feet my jaw was on the floor and then come to find out it wasn't real it was just a commercial for some *investment* company I was bawling tears even looking at this I wanna cry Christopher Reeve was only 52 when he passed away in 2004 from cardiac arrest less than a year later his wife Dana was diagnosed with lung cancer even though she never smoked a year and a half after Christopher passed away Dana passed away leaving Will without parents at 13 years old this was so well done I'm still recovering his children are gorgeous and Will  is on Good Morning America to make your heart ache even more someone in this film says if Christopher was still alive Robin still would be too
